WHEELER et al. v. PLUMAS COUNTY. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 4, 1903.) No. 833. In Error to the Circuit Court of the United States for the Northern District of California. A. E. Cheney, T. C. Campbell, and W. H. Metson, for plaintiffs in error. U. S. Webb, for defendant in error.

Before GILBERT and ROSS, Circuit Judges, and HAW-LEY, District Judge.

HAWLEY, District Judge.

This case presents substantially the same questions that are discussed and decided in Flanigan v. County of Sierra (C. C. A.) 122 Fed. 24; and upon the authority of that case-the judgment of the Circuit Court is affirmed, with costs.
